Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay medium-coarse light brown; purple-brown core. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) contains several such drawings Name Agelo(chos). From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0035.23 and British Museum 1925,0119.329 and 2011,5003.255, 258 and 273.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0403)
